Henry Ford invented the first automobile. He was an American engineer who founded the Ford Motor Company, and is considered one of the most groundbreaking and influential inventors of the 20th century. Ford's innovation of the Model T was a major step forward for the automotive industry, and his invention revolutionized transportation worldwide. Ford is also credited with popularizing the assembly line method of automobile manufacturing, which significantly lowered the cost and time required to produce each vehicle. Ford's accomplishments and legacy have made him an iconic figure in American history, and his impact on society is still felt today.